    "comment": "Rationale: KA2 (kainate) receptor.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has ligand-gated ion channel receptor activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (shown with high-resolution technique). The inference to term ligand-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099507) is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[Q61626] SyNGO ID 1121 (PMID:12954862, EM). Experimental description: For these experiments, the GluK4 plasmid from the Heinemann laboratory was subcloned into the pCIneo vector (Promega Corporation, Madison, WI, USA) for use in mammalian cells.\n\n29/6/2018 Pim\n- I have selected 'human' as the species of the expressed protein. The leader of the lab that contributed the cDNA (Heinemann SF) passed away several years ago.",
